description:
Firefox 132 web browser is now available for public beta testing with support for blocking third-party cookie access and HTTP-favicons, WebRender hardware accelerated rendering for most SVG Filter Primitives, and other changes. Here's what to expect!

The post Firefox 132 Enters Beta with Support for Blocking Third-Party Cookie Access appeared first on 9to5Linux - do not reproduce this article without permission. This RSS feed is intended for readers, not scrapers.
title: Firefox 132 Enters Beta with Support for Blocking Third-Party Cookie Access
